#t
Install ZSH and make it pretty (on Arch Linux)

#b
Eli Saado

#n
* A computer with Arch Linux (or variants, like Antergos)
* A working internet connection

#s
1. Update the pacman repositories (`sudo pacman -Syu`)
2. Install zsh (`sudo pacman -S zsh`)
3. Install grml-zsh-config (`sudo pacman -S grml-zsh-config`)
4. Install zsh-syntax-highlighting (`sudo pacman -S zsh-syntax-highlighting`)
5. Add `source /usr/share/zsh/plugins/zsh-syntax-highlighting/zsh-syntax-highlighting.zsh` to the end of your ~/.zshrc, if the zshrc doesn't exist, create it.
6. Run `chsh`, enter your password and make the default shell `/usr/bin/zsh`.
7. Log in and out (or reboot) to apply the changes.
8. Done!
